cs.NI, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper is about programming data-plane algorithms for network switches, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). It also involves designing a programming language (cs.PL) and compiling it to a specific hardware architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the implementation of algorithms for congestion control, load balancing, and queue management, which are related to system and control theory (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
